(define a 3) is a definition not an expression
(set! a 3) is an expression
(begin ...) and (if ...) they need expressions not definitions

racket have definitions and expressions, no statements
also racket have some control forms, like require that's not a definition or and expression
http://docs.racket-lang.org/reference/syntax-model.html?q=fully#%28part._fully-expanded%29
expr = id

python or c have statements and expressions,

statements have side-effect, expressions only return vaules, no side-effect
